WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:02.636
Previously on The Riches.

00:02.670 --> 00:04.405
Do you really think
Dad has a plan?

00:04.438 --> 00:06.807
He stole the money.
Ma lost the money.

00:06.840 --> 00:10.144
And now we're here
in a dead guy's house.

00:10.178 --> 00:12.613
- [ Wayne ]
Doug Rich was a litigator.
- Hi. Doug Rich.

00:12.646 --> 00:15.516
You have to be the worst
lawyer in the world.

00:15.549 --> 00:18.652
I am. And you--
You're fired.

00:18.686 --> 00:20.688
The new guy
doesn't know anything!

00:20.721 --> 00:23.457
You wanna be a partner?
That's what I went to
law school for.

00:23.491 --> 00:26.194
Okay, man.
In the meantime, you need to
invite me to a dinner.

00:26.227 --> 00:29.330
A dinner?
I check out your house,
your friends, your family,

00:29.363 --> 00:31.299
see if you're
partnership material.

00:31.332 --> 00:33.201
[ Dahlia ]
This is Chunky Kay.

00:33.234 --> 00:36.137
She was my cellie in prison.

00:36.170 --> 00:38.372
Man, this whole maid thing's
really weirdin' me out.

00:38.406 --> 00:40.474
If I don't work for you,
I gotta work for somebody.

00:40.508 --> 00:43.744
I want you to think
of three adjectives that
describe Doug and Cherien.

00:43.777 --> 00:47.148
And if I like your adjectives,
I'm gonna make Doug here
a partner. If I don't,

00:47.181 --> 00:48.482
he's out on the street.

00:48.516 --> 00:52.220
- [ Sniffing ]
- Jesus Christ.

00:52.253 --> 00:55.389
- Shut the goddamn door!
- You want to make me a partner
right now? Right here?

00:55.423 --> 00:58.492
[ Hugh ]
Why the hell not?
Maybe later.

00:59.160 --> 01:02.630
I wanted to be a partner.
Something about it
makes me sick to my stomach.

01:02.663 --> 01:04.532
Well, we're turnin'
into buffers, baby.

01:04.565 --> 01:06.234
You want some?

01:06.267 --> 01:07.768
No.

01:07.801 --> 01:09.737
If you decide
you do want some,

01:09.770 --> 01:12.406
I'll just leave it
right there for you.

01:12.440 --> 01:14.242
[ Dahlia ]
Don't.
So stop me then.

01:19.713 --> 01:21.549
[ Birds Chirping ]
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

01:40.501 --> 01:42.503
Why didn't you
come to bed last night?

01:42.536 --> 01:45.139
Huh? What's the matter
with you?

01:45.173 --> 01:47.441
I saw the little baggie
your friend Kay
passed you last night,

01:47.475 --> 01:49.377
the one with
the white powder in it.

01:49.410 --> 01:51.479
She left it here.

01:51.512 --> 01:53.447
I just can't take
the lying.

01:53.481 --> 01:56.350
That's what I can't take.

01:56.384 --> 02:00.254
- I'm not lying, Wayne.
I told you. I'm off that shit.
- Really?

02:00.288 --> 02:01.655
Yeah.
'Cause after
you went to sleep,

02:01.689 --> 02:05.193
I went around the house,
and I found about 15 bottles
of tranquilizer...

02:05.226 --> 02:06.894
hidden all
over the place.

02:06.927 --> 02:09.863
You must be
the most tranquil person
on the goddamn planet.

02:09.897 --> 02:14.335
Has it ever crossed your mind
I might need it
to get off the meth?

02:14.368 --> 02:18.539
Well, why didn't you tell me?

02:18.572 --> 02:21.509
Because maybe
I did not think
you would understand.

02:21.542 --> 02:23.711
Bet Hugh understands.
You do it with him too?

02:23.744 --> 02:25.713
Oh, my God. Jesus.

02:25.746 --> 02:28.416
Isn't it enough that
I'm not taking
the shit anymore? Huh?

02:28.449 --> 02:30.284
What do you
want from me?
[ Sam ] Mom, Dad,

02:30.318 --> 02:32.486
I need somebody to sign
my permission slip.

02:34.522 --> 02:38.226
Science museum, huh?
Yeah, we're seeing an exhibit
on global warming.

02:38.259 --> 02:40.261
Don't you need to
get to work?

02:40.294 --> 02:42.530
I don't know.

02:42.563 --> 02:44.265
- Probably.
- Dad, are you gonna
quit your job?

02:44.298 --> 02:45.366
I don't know.

02:51.605 --> 02:53.274
I don't know.
Is that why...

02:53.307 --> 02:54.975
you were sleeping on the floor
in my room last night?

02:55.008 --> 02:56.777
Because you're gonna quit?

02:56.810 --> 02:59.947
I think that's
between him and Mom.
No. No, it's not about Mom.

02:59.980 --> 03:03.384
I was just thinking
life is too short
to work for assholes.

03:04.485 --> 03:06.454
Remember that.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.489
Calm down.
There's a million
buffer jobs out there.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.859
It says here they're looking
for a cashier at Wiener Hut.

03:11.892 --> 03:14.828
Sammy, there's no way that
anybody in Edenfalls could
live on minimum wage, okay?

03:14.862 --> 03:18.366
- Just forget that.
- Would you relax?
I'm Doug Rich.

03:18.399 --> 03:20.734
I'm a high-profile lawyer,
okay?

03:20.768 --> 03:24.538
I've settled two major cases.
Hell, I'm a member of
Edenfalls Country Club,

03:24.572 --> 03:26.374
and your mom's still
got the job at Panco.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.542
Dahlia.
You're gonna be late.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.812
Dahlia?

03:36.417 --> 03:38.319
Dahlia?

03:39.520 --> 03:41.455
Coming.

04:25.366 --> 04:27.601
Oh, no. No, no.
No. Hey.

04:27.635 --> 04:29.870
I was gonna flush it!
I was gonna flush it!

04:29.903 --> 04:32.473
I was! I swear!
I was gonna flush it.

04:32.506 --> 04:34.642
How big a supply is this?

04:34.675 --> 04:37.445
A month? A week?
No. You gotta believe me.
I was gonna flush it.

04:37.478 --> 04:40.080
You gotta believe me.
If you're gonna do this shit,
I'm gonna do it too.

04:40.113 --> 04:42.583
No. I was gonna
flush it, Wayne. No! No!

04:42.616 --> 04:44.552
[ Grunts ]

04:45.853 --> 04:47.821
Now I believe you.

04:47.855 --> 04:49.723
God!
[ Coughing ]

04:49.757 --> 04:52.626
[ Breathing Heavily ]

04:57.130 --> 04:59.066
God!

05:24.925 --> 05:27.395
Are you crazy?
[ Wayne Coughing ]

05:28.596 --> 05:30.898
I mean, are you
trying to kill yourself?

05:30.931 --> 05:33.100
I don't know. Are you?

05:33.133 --> 05:37.705
Of all the assaholic
things you have ever done,
this is the most assaholic!

05:37.738 --> 05:40.007
Are you aware of how much
of this shit you did?

05:40.040 --> 05:43.677
I am so sorry. I forgot to read
the Crankhead's Handbook.

05:43.711 --> 05:46.046
[ Coughing ]
Oh, yeah. It burns.

05:46.079 --> 05:48.682
That's right.
That shit is lethal, Wayne.

05:48.716 --> 05:51.585
You better get to work,
'cause I think I quit.

05:51.619 --> 05:56.457
[ Breathing Heavily ]
Jesus Christ.

05:56.490 --> 06:00.027
Okay. If you let the kids
see you like this,
I'm gonna rip your nuts off.

06:00.060 --> 06:03.731
I can't tell if I'm enjoying
your reaction because
it's actually gratifying...

06:03.764 --> 06:05.699
or 'cause
the meth is kickin' in.

06:08.168 --> 06:11.038
[ Inhales ]

06:11.071 --> 06:12.973
[ Exhales ]
Jesus.

06:16.677 --> 06:19.179
[ Sam ]
Mortgage: four grand a month.

06:19.212 --> 06:23.417
Uh, Rosemere Academy
is $4,500 a month.

06:23.451 --> 06:26.554
Um, Edenfalls Country Club
is a thousand dollars a month.

06:26.587 --> 06:28.756
Temple membership.
Water, electric, telephone.

06:28.789 --> 06:31.191
Sam. Will you stop, okay?
He's not gonna quit.

06:31.224 --> 06:34.628
He might. Somethin' went down
with him and Mom at that party.

06:34.662 --> 06:39.633
Okay. Why are we gettin' a bill
from Mountain View Nursing Home
for $4,700 a month?

06:39.667 --> 06:42.836
Must be where Cherien's mother
is. He was never gonna make it
in the corporate world anyway.

06:42.870 --> 06:46.039
- God knows Mom's
not gonna hang on to a job.
- So, what are we gonna do?

06:46.073 --> 06:48.108
What we always do.
Move somewhere else.
And-- And what?

06:48.141 --> 06:50.578
Go back to stealing wallets
and rippin' off car stereos?

06:50.611 --> 06:52.546
Yeah, maybe you can wear
a mustache this time.

06:52.580 --> 06:54.748
You see, that sounds
really fun to me.

06:54.782 --> 07:00.020
Okay. Does Mom make
$14,723.51 per month?

07:00.053 --> 07:02.055
'Cause that's what
we're gonna need.

07:02.089 --> 07:05.959
That's after taxes, buddy.
You gotta add 35%.

07:05.993 --> 07:08.696
Okay. Do not go upstairs.
Your dad has food poisoning.

07:08.729 --> 07:13.667
Mom, do you make $19,876.74--
Do not go upstairs.

07:13.701 --> 07:15.636
Okay?

07:29.750 --> 07:31.652
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

07:34.287 --> 07:36.189
[ Engine Starts ]

08:03.216 --> 08:05.686
- [ Kimmie ] Where's Doug?
- Hey. Doug.

08:05.719 --> 08:09.557
Hey. It's me.
Uh, are you there?

08:09.590 --> 08:12.292
I know you're there.
I just want to make sure
you're still alive, huh?

08:12.325 --> 08:14.595
No. Oh, he had bad clams.

08:14.628 --> 08:16.897
Would you call me, you asshole.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.266
So, Doug's not comin' in?
Who the hell cares?

08:19.299 --> 08:21.802
Uh, Hugh does.
He called from Reno.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.872
The REIT is gonna be here at
9:00 for the closing. He needs
Doug to answer questions.

08:24.905 --> 08:27.575
The REIT?
The Real Estate
Investment Trust.

08:27.608 --> 08:30.544
They're buying
that office tower. Hugh left
the papers on his desk.

08:30.578 --> 08:32.813
Okay. Um, well,
I'll handle that.

08:32.846 --> 08:36.116
Now, Kimmie, you know how to
work the Google thing, huh?

08:36.149 --> 08:39.920
Can you find out what a person's
supposed to do if another person
does a whole shitload of meth?

08:39.953 --> 08:42.723
- Is it the one where
you pack their head in ice?
- Huh?

08:44.858 --> 08:47.828
I'm-- I'm givin'
an antidrug talk
at my kids' school.

08:47.861 --> 08:50.297
- Oh.
- Okay?

08:50.330 --> 08:52.600
[ Beeping ]
Okay.

08:52.633 --> 08:57.170
[ Ringing ]
My monthly expenses
are $19,000!

08:57.204 --> 09:00.040
[ Wayne's Voice ]
Hi. This is the Riches.
We're not here at the moment.

09:00.073 --> 09:03.944
$19,000! Ninet--

09:03.977 --> 09:06.914
I gotta get a job.
[ Dahlia ]
Wayne?

09:06.947 --> 09:11.018
Wayne. Wayne.
Pick up the goddamn phone.

09:11.051 --> 09:13.253
Wayne, it's me.
Pick up the phone.

09:13.286 --> 09:16.323
I understand you got
a hiring freeze, Craig.
[ Dahlia ] I know you're there.

09:16.356 --> 09:18.992
[ Craig ] It's not just
the hiring freeze, Doug.
[ Dahlia ] You're high, Wayne.

09:19.026 --> 09:22.229
- [ Beeps ]
- "Extreme euphoria,
anxiety, aggressiveness,

09:22.262 --> 09:26.934
hostility, paranoia, mania,
excessive talkativeness."

09:26.967 --> 09:30.871
It doesn't say what
to do, but-- Oh, check out
the symptoms of overdose.

09:30.904 --> 09:35.809
"Nerve damage, kidney failure,
convulsions, hallucinations,
stroke, heart attack."

09:35.843 --> 09:38.311
That ought to scare
the kids, huh?
Yeah.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.850
You better go in there.
They're gonna have questions.

09:42.883 --> 09:45.953
Okay. Call Doug.
You read him
that list of symptoms.

09:45.986 --> 09:50.123
'Cause he's gonna have to do
the drug talk for the kids.
[ Sniffs ]

09:50.157 --> 09:54.662
[ Kimmie On Answering Machine ]
Doug? Doug, Cherien wanted me
to read you these symptoms.

09:54.695 --> 09:58.966
"Aggressiveness,
hostility, paranoia,
excessive talkativeness"--

09:58.999 --> 10:02.703
Shit.
"rapid breathing,
extreme sex drive,

10:02.736 --> 10:05.706
sweating,
heart palpitations"--

10:05.739 --> 10:08.642
Okay. Uh--

10:08.676 --> 10:10.978
These here.
All right.

10:11.011 --> 10:15.248
So, I'm gonna, uh,
notarize the stuff.

10:15.282 --> 10:18.285
Uh, Panetta said
we should talk to head of
Legal before we sign.

10:18.318 --> 10:21.354
Well, the head of Legal
kicked it upstairs to me.

10:23.156 --> 10:26.259
$19,000. I mean, how
the hell did I get here?

10:26.293 --> 10:29.663
[ Woman ] I hear ya.
And that's before you're blowing
45 grand a year on college.

10:29.697 --> 10:32.065
Forty-five grand?
I mean, how the hell
do you pay it?

10:32.099 --> 10:34.367
Took out a second
and a third mortgage.
Goddamn it.

10:34.401 --> 10:38.806
Look, Doug. I wish we had
an opening here, but the truth
is, even if we did have one--

10:38.839 --> 10:40.941
Look, I know. I'm not
a defense litigator, but--

10:40.974 --> 10:43.176
[ Woman ]
I hate to sound harsh,
but we need someone--

10:43.210 --> 10:45.746
[ Scoffs ]
Shouldn't we
read 'em first?

10:45.779 --> 10:48.115
Sure. Whatever
blows your hair back.

10:56.456 --> 10:59.793
[ Overlapping Voices ]
Don't need anyone right now.
Not now. Not now. No. No. No.

10:59.827 --> 11:01.161
God.

11:07.968 --> 11:10.804
"We'd like to thank you
for giving us the opportunity
to meet with us.

11:10.838 --> 11:13.306
It was a pleasure
to discuss the"--
Hayden-Javitz!

11:13.340 --> 11:15.876
"We're so sorry you declined
to accept this position.
Should you ever recons--"

11:17.244 --> 11:20.180
[ Beeping, Line Ringing ]

11:20.213 --> 11:21.882
[ Woman ]
Law office.
Hayden-Javitz?

11:21.915 --> 11:24.818
Just to put your kid through
one year of college
costs $45,000.

11:24.852 --> 11:27.154
And I didn't even
go to college.

11:27.187 --> 11:31.324
Of course I went to college.
I went to...

11:31.358 --> 11:34.461
Georgetown University
to do my college degree,

11:34.494 --> 11:39.132
and then I went to Har--
Princeton University,
and I studied law again.

11:39.166 --> 11:41.969
I have done a lot of
extracurricular activities.

11:42.002 --> 11:45.906
I was in an eating club
where we ate a lot of food.
That's the thing you do there.

11:45.939 --> 11:48.441
And I was in-- was
Prince Dauntless in Once Upon
a Time on a Mattress.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.911
I was a very excellent
leading man.

11:50.944 --> 11:55.482
Dear God, you may ask,
why I put that on my résumé.
I ask why I put it on my résumé.

11:55.515 --> 11:57.751
But it's on the résumé
to show you who I am.

11:57.785 --> 12:00.187
If I could just talk to
Mr. Javitz, I could explain--
Fine.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.791
I'll call the managing
partner and I'll ask
if he'll see you, okay?

12:03.824 --> 12:05.458
Just please have a seat.
I will.

12:07.995 --> 12:10.030
Please.

12:10.063 --> 12:13.333
[ Line Ringing ]

12:13.366 --> 12:17.370
I have a-- a Mr. Rich
out here in the lobby with
a file of wrinkled-up papers,

12:17.404 --> 12:19.973
saying he wants to
meet you.

12:20.007 --> 12:23.143
[ Line Ringing ]
[ Dahlia ]
Wayne, where the hell are you?

12:23.176 --> 12:25.846
Do you have any idea
how much your mother's
nursing home costs?

12:25.879 --> 12:28.148
My mother's been dead
for 32 years.

12:28.181 --> 12:30.450
Mr. Rich,

12:30.483 --> 12:32.953
our managing partner
said he'd be
delighted to see you.

12:38.058 --> 12:40.093
Um, I have
Doug Rich for you.

12:41.261 --> 12:43.263
[ Exhales ]

12:45.165 --> 12:47.367
Stewart. Holy shit!

12:47.400 --> 12:49.469
I know. What are the odds?

12:49.502 --> 12:52.139
Last time I saw you,
you were all blurry...

12:52.172 --> 12:54.808
'cause one of Panco's
security goons was macing me.

12:54.842 --> 12:57.811
No hard feelings, man.

12:57.845 --> 13:00.080
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.282
Whoa.

13:02.315 --> 13:05.052
Hey. You got my job.
I got yours.
Goes around, comes around.

13:05.085 --> 13:08.388
Whoa! Whoa.
That is--

13:08.421 --> 13:10.958
Boy, that is really big.
That is really,
really big, you know?

13:10.991 --> 13:13.493
[ Laughing ]
I fired you, man.

13:13.526 --> 13:15.829
Nah. That was Hugh's thing.

13:15.863 --> 13:18.598
- Survival of the fittest.
- Well, talk about Darwinian.

13:18.631 --> 13:21.168
You know how much it costs
to send your kids to college?

13:21.201 --> 13:25.105
It never ends.
[ Chuckles ]
Friggin' gerbil wheel.

13:25.138 --> 13:29.042
A sickness.
We Americans never feel
like we have enough.

13:29.076 --> 13:30.978
- Why do you think that is?
- I don't know.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.446
Think it has to do with
that goddamn Puritan work ethic?

13:33.480 --> 13:36.116
- Huh? Workin' and
workin' and workin'?
- Absolutely.

13:36.149 --> 13:38.518
It all goes back to
that psychotic dickhead
Myles Standish.

13:38.551 --> 13:40.988
You know, he--
You know he was
only 4 foot 11?

13:41.021 --> 13:43.123
[ Chuckles ]
I mean! You know?

13:43.156 --> 13:48.929
A major Puritan, and 400 years
later, we're still dealing
with his short guy complex.

13:48.962 --> 13:51.231
We gotta stop the madness, huh?

13:51.264 --> 13:54.301
- We gotta say, "I have enough."
- I have enough.

13:54.334 --> 13:56.336
[ Chuckles ]
You know what isn't enough,
though, Doug?

13:58.271 --> 13:59.572
Your new job here.

14:01.374 --> 14:04.211
As a janitor.

14:04.244 --> 14:06.346
Yeah?
Yeah. A janitor.

14:06.379 --> 14:08.548
You lousy prick.

14:08.581 --> 14:11.251
Nobody fires my ass.

14:11.284 --> 14:13.153
Now get the hell
out of my office.

14:13.186 --> 14:16.089
- You little shit!
- Security!

14:16.123 --> 14:19.893
Hey! Get off!
Hey! He is a total fraud!

14:19.927 --> 14:22.896
Look at the pictures
in his office.
They're not even his kids.

14:22.930 --> 14:24.464
That's-- That's--
That's my résumé.

14:29.602 --> 14:31.504
[ Chattering ]

14:35.375 --> 14:37.911
I am...

14:37.945 --> 14:41.681
unclear on item 15 sub "A."

14:41.714 --> 14:43.483
Mm-hmm? Okay.

14:47.487 --> 14:49.589
[ Buzzing, Chirping ]
Excuse me.

14:49.622 --> 14:51.658
Wayne? Where are you?

14:51.691 --> 14:54.227
Do you know how much
we pay for HBO?

14:56.463 --> 15:00.167
Okay. Wayne, do not
give me shit about HBO.
Where the hell are you?

15:00.200 --> 15:02.335
I'm here.

15:02.369 --> 15:04.304
- I've had a wake-up call,
Dahlia.
- Where are you?

15:04.337 --> 15:06.006
We don't need
any of this shit.

15:06.039 --> 15:08.608
It is time to say enough.

15:08.641 --> 15:11.344
Wayne, will you just tell me,
are you having chest pains?
Okay?

15:11.378 --> 15:14.347
And where'd you put
all the goddamn pills?
Did you throw 'em all out?

15:14.381 --> 15:16.383
Did you throw out
the ones underneath
the garden gnome?

15:16.416 --> 15:18.518
If you didn't, would you
please take five of 'em?
Fine.

15:18.551 --> 15:21.521
- But we gotta cut out HBO.
- HBO.

15:21.554 --> 15:23.690
We gotta stop
drinking those lattes.

15:23.723 --> 15:28.095
We gotta stop using
cell phones and the Internet
and the cable, and we--

15:28.128 --> 15:30.964
we gotta reuse paper towels,
'cause you know what?

15:30.998 --> 15:33.633
Nobody wants Doug Rich.

15:33.666 --> 15:37.704
- Oh, my God.
- He is an old, sleazy,
washed-up nothing.

15:37.737 --> 15:40.473
- Okay.
- But that's okay, 'cause we
don't need any of this shit.

15:40.507 --> 15:42.409
Wayne. Wayne.
You know?

15:42.442 --> 15:45.712
- The Pilgrims didn't even
have paper towels.
- Wayne.

15:45.745 --> 15:48.048
You wouldn't have had Squanto
sitting on the edge
of Plymouth Rock...

15:48.081 --> 15:50.083
watching HBO,
for God's sakes, or...

15:50.117 --> 15:53.586
paying a nursing home
$4,700 a month.

15:53.620 --> 15:56.056
- Jesus Christ!
- Wayne!

15:56.089 --> 15:59.226
[ Clicks, Dial Tone ]
Shit.

15:59.259 --> 16:02.562
[ Wayne On Phone ]
$2,300 for a single room?

16:02.595 --> 16:04.764
What are you,
the Ritz-Carlton?

16:04.797 --> 16:08.201
- You pay a premium for privacy.
- She doesn't like privacy.
She likes lots of people.

16:08.235 --> 16:10.437
I mean, she--
she's lonely.
[ Computer Chirps ]

16:10.470 --> 16:14.074
Mom is very, very lonely.

16:14.107 --> 16:17.477
You know the search for
individual freedom, which--
and I'm quoting Mom here--

16:17.510 --> 16:19.712
has led to a culture
of alienation and anomie,

16:19.746 --> 16:22.582
which ironically leads us
to spend more and more money...

16:22.615 --> 16:25.285
trying to fill
the howling, aching--
[ Beeps ]

16:25.318 --> 16:27.620
empty--
[ Typing ]

16:27.654 --> 16:29.656
Are y--
Are you answering e-mails?

16:29.689 --> 16:32.192
I'm multitasking, Mr. Rich.
What do you want?

16:32.225 --> 16:35.495
I want to know what the hell
this medical charge is
for 1,580.22.

16:35.528 --> 16:38.165
We had to put
Dr. Morganstern on oxygen.

16:38.198 --> 16:40.067
Paying for her doctor's
medical bills as well?

16:40.100 --> 16:45.105
Your mother-in-law
is Dr. Morganstern,
and she needs oxygen.

16:45.138 --> 16:47.207
Oh. Oh.
So you're charging her
to breathe now.

16:47.240 --> 16:49.709
Well, that's illegal.
She doesn't want to
live like that.

16:49.742 --> 16:52.145
Hooked up to an oxygen tent--
what kind of life is that?

16:52.179 --> 16:54.547
Tell her it'll be okay
if she lets go.

16:54.581 --> 16:58.251
You know? Tell her to let go.
Tell her to go towards
the light. They love that.

16:58.285 --> 17:00.087
[ Clicks, Dial Tone ]
Tell-- Hello?

17:03.323 --> 17:06.259
I just need a little
clearing up on article 41.

17:06.293 --> 17:09.729
Okay. You know what?
I don't give a good goddamn
about article 41, buddy.

17:09.762 --> 17:12.199
[ Chuckles ]

17:12.232 --> 17:14.767
I have to say...

17:14.801 --> 17:19.339
I think we've been really
good sports about the lack
of clarity in these documents.

17:19.372 --> 17:22.575
[ Exhales ]
Okay.

17:22.609 --> 17:26.146
I'm sorry. Sorry.

17:26.179 --> 17:28.515
I have a relative with
some addiction problems.

17:29.816 --> 17:31.784
Oh.

17:31.818 --> 17:35.355
- I'm sorry.
- Yeah. Okay.

17:35.388 --> 17:38.558
Shit. Let's look at
article 41.

17:41.461 --> 17:43.663
You know, uh--
[ Clears Throat ]
I, uh--

17:43.696 --> 17:45.665
I hope this doesn't
cross the line, but...

17:45.698 --> 17:48.601
you've seemed quite upset
all morning, and...

17:48.635 --> 17:50.670
I just want to say...

17:50.703 --> 17:53.506
my son's had some
addiction issues.

17:53.540 --> 17:55.508
He's been
in and out of rehab.

17:55.542 --> 18:00.413
Well, I just mean that I--
I know how it can
rip your guts out.

18:12.392 --> 18:14.294
Can you not read the sign?

18:17.330 --> 18:19.432
Says "No Solicitors."

18:19.466 --> 18:21.901
Uh, I can read.

18:21.934 --> 18:25.538
Um, I just thought you might
like to know that your-- your
roof is lookin' a little tired.

18:25.572 --> 18:28.275
Please don't make me
call Security.
Uh, I--

18:28.308 --> 18:31.144
I also-- I also do
house painting and hauling.

18:31.178 --> 18:33.513
I've already availed
my services to some of
your neighbors.

18:33.546 --> 18:36.349
Your-- Your backdoor
neighbor in 1405.

18:36.383 --> 18:38.851
Doug Rich?
No. No. That's not his name.

18:38.885 --> 18:42.155
Uh, fella with a beard,
three kids, big old
Mercedes-Benz in the driveway.

18:42.189 --> 18:45.625
Yeah. That's Doug Rich.
That's his name?
You sure about that?

18:45.658 --> 18:49.162
Well, I think I would remember
his name. That prick screwed me
out of $10 million.

18:49.196 --> 18:52.265
Ten million dollars?

18:52.299 --> 18:55.735
Doug Rich screwed you
out of $10 million?
Mm-hmm.

18:55.768 --> 18:57.270
You were robbed.
That is--

18:57.304 --> 19:00.440
That is a gross overcharge
for aluminum siding.

19:00.473 --> 19:04.211
Do I look like someone
who uses aluminum sidin'?

19:04.244 --> 19:07.647
He's a lawyer.
That shit-suckin' bastard.

19:09.916 --> 19:13.786
Would you care
for a fresh latte, Dale?

19:16.489 --> 19:20.460
We do not euthanize
our patients, sir.
Read our mission statement.

19:20.493 --> 19:24.431
I am just trying to understand
what is this charge for $279.50
for miscellaneous?

19:24.464 --> 19:27.600
Miscellaneous
is the cappuccino cart.

19:27.634 --> 19:30.303
- She bought
a cappuccino cart?
- We have a cappuccino cart.

19:30.337 --> 19:33.640
It's one of our perks.
Dear God. You must be peeling
the old bat off the ceiling.

19:33.673 --> 19:36.876
I mean, why can't
she just rip some bark
off a tree and chew it?

19:36.909 --> 19:39.979
I mean, it's probably
what Squanto used to do.
Didn't cost him a dime.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.915
- Bark is a natural stimulant.
- You want your mother-in-law
to chew bark?

19:43.916 --> 19:45.752
Okay. You tell her.

19:45.785 --> 19:48.221
Front desk,
visitor for Dr. Morganstern.

19:48.255 --> 19:51.291
No, no, no. Not now.
I don't want to scare her.
Look.

19:51.324 --> 19:53.360
She's elderly and obviously
over-caffeinated.

19:53.393 --> 19:55.728
You know? This is just
a recipe for cardiac arrest.
[ Clears Throat ]

20:00.700 --> 20:03.536
[ Man ]
Too much foam, dear.

20:03.570 --> 20:06.639
She doesn't want to see me.
She hates lawyers.

20:06.673 --> 20:08.875
I mean, Mom has had it
with the litigious society.

20:08.908 --> 20:10.810
Chances are she won't even
remember you, Mr. Rich.

20:10.843 --> 20:12.945
We had to move her
to Ward "C."

20:14.514 --> 20:16.449
Dr. Morganstern? Hon?

20:16.483 --> 20:18.518
[ Sniffs ]

20:18.551 --> 20:19.952
Your son-in-law
is here.

20:24.624 --> 20:27.760
Dr. Morganstern?
Mmm, Mother?

20:27.794 --> 20:29.696
Hi, it's Doug.

20:31.298 --> 20:32.832
I've had some work done.

20:34.000 --> 20:35.568
Mom?

20:37.337 --> 20:40.507
Sometimes you have to
speak up a little.

20:40.540 --> 20:43.543
Hi, Mom.
It's Doug.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.912
Doug Rich. You remember?

20:45.945 --> 20:50.283
- Who?
- Doug.

20:50.317 --> 20:52.319
- Doug Rich.
- I'm Doug Rich.

20:53.320 --> 20:55.488
I'm Doug Rich. I think--

20:55.522 --> 20:57.657
I think you're--
you're Marvin O'Keiffe, sir.

20:57.690 --> 20:59.392
I'm Doug Rich.

20:59.426 --> 21:01.294
What is this, Spartacus?
I'm Doug Rich.

21:01.328 --> 21:03.730
Do not antagonize
Mr. O'Keiffe.

21:03.763 --> 21:05.398
You lousy sack of shit!

21:05.432 --> 21:07.434
I'm Doug Rich.

21:07.467 --> 21:09.869
Maybe you are Doug Rich.

21:09.902 --> 21:11.871
Is that why I'm not
getting any jobs?

21:11.904 --> 21:14.374
You're causing me
to be unemployed.

21:14.407 --> 21:18.711
You're causing the supply
of Doug Rich to greatly exceed
the demand for Doug Rich.

21:18.745 --> 21:21.681
Yeah. That's it.

21:21.714 --> 21:24.884
Why is there no air in here?
Come on, Ma.

21:24.917 --> 21:29.822
- We're getting out of here.
- Mr. Rich. She's not covered
without a day release form.

21:29.856 --> 21:31.891
We're going.

21:31.924 --> 21:33.826
Thank you, Doug.

21:38.531 --> 21:40.700
This is great.

21:40.733 --> 21:43.670
This is a great idea.
This is a great idea.

21:43.703 --> 21:46.439
We're just gonna
get some air.

21:46.473 --> 21:48.908
[ Inhales Deeply ]

21:48.941 --> 21:51.378
You all right there, Ma?

21:53.045 --> 21:55.114
[ Inhales Deeply ]

21:55.147 --> 21:57.684
Isn't this fun, Ma?

21:57.717 --> 22:00.720
Okay. I'll put that--
Here we go.

22:00.753 --> 22:03.790
We're gonna get some air.
I bet you like this air.

22:03.823 --> 22:06.593
This is real air, Mom.
[ Moans ]

22:06.626 --> 22:10.397
Got ya. I got ya.

22:10.430 --> 22:12.932
I got ya.
Okay. This is fun, huh?

22:14.734 --> 22:18.571
Down.
[ Mutters ]
Watch your head there.

22:18.605 --> 22:21.073
Back you go. Whoa.
[ Chuckles ]
Not so far back.

22:21.107 --> 22:23.376
Huh?
You have to go here.

22:23.410 --> 22:26.546
It's like a ride.
Here we go.

22:26.579 --> 22:28.681
Okay.

22:31.117 --> 22:33.352
[ Warning Tone Chiming ]

22:35.054 --> 22:36.823
I made some calls.

22:36.856 --> 22:38.791
What?

22:44.130 --> 22:47.066
Yeah, yeah.
Excellent plan.

22:47.099 --> 22:50.002
Where's Cherien?
Cherien?

22:50.036 --> 22:52.104
Look, what kind of
doctor are you anyway?

22:52.138 --> 22:54.874
Tell me all about that.
Where is Cherien?

22:54.907 --> 22:57.444
No, no, no.
We go to the park.
What about that?

22:57.477 --> 23:00.046
Do you want to
go to the park?
We could feed the ducks.

23:00.079 --> 23:04.917
- Where is Cherien?
- All right. I'll take you
to Cherien, but...

23:04.951 --> 23:07.086
she's changed.

23:07.119 --> 23:09.956
She's changed an awful lot.
More than me.

23:09.989 --> 23:11.991
Okay?

23:14.694 --> 23:16.896
And now...

23:16.929 --> 23:21.534
he's living with some skank
in Little Rock with maroon hair.

23:21.568 --> 23:25.438
[ Sniffling ]
And "Satan" tattooed
on her neck.

23:25.472 --> 23:26.639
[ Sobbing ]

23:28.475 --> 23:30.877
Oh. Hey. Hold that thought.

23:30.910 --> 23:33.546
[ Wayne ]
I need the stuff. Just lattes.
Where the hell have you been?

23:33.580 --> 23:35.682
Got a surprise in the car.
What happened to your suit?

23:35.715 --> 23:37.950
Oh, it's a minor altercation.
It's good. It's good.

23:37.984 --> 23:40.520
Really cleared things up.
Everything is totally clear.

23:40.553 --> 23:42.855
This is a bad sign.
That is a very bad sign.

23:42.889 --> 23:44.824
No. It's a great sign,
'cause everything
finally makes sense.

23:44.857 --> 23:46.859
Everything is not
supposed to make sense.

23:46.893 --> 23:49.028
If it makes sense
and everything is beautiful--

23:49.061 --> 23:52.131
Everything is beautiful.
Okay. You see, now you're
tweakin'. All right?

23:52.164 --> 23:55.134
This is very dangerous, Wayne.
All these are just symptoms,
okay?

23:55.167 --> 23:57.704
These are symptoms.
Euphoria, aggression,

23:57.737 --> 24:00.907
heart palpitations, extreme
sex drive-- all these things
you're feeling right now.

24:00.940 --> 24:03.643
Pretty soon you're gonna crash,
you're gonna get
suicidally depressed,

24:03.676 --> 24:06.879
then you're maybe
gonna feel like there's bugs
crawling all over your skin.

24:06.913 --> 24:09.882
Oh, I'm so glad you're better.
I was all worried.

24:09.916 --> 24:12.051
Kimmie.
Oh. Oh.

24:12.084 --> 24:14.787
I once ate bad herring,
and I had the trots for a week.
[ Chuckles ]

24:14.821 --> 24:17.223
Oh, God. That means so much.

24:17.256 --> 24:20.727
I mean, so many people don't
give a shit about Doug Rich.
Okay. That's--

24:20.760 --> 24:22.595
[ Dahlia ] Okay. That's enough.
[ Wayne ]
Mmm!

24:22.629 --> 24:24.731
Oh.
That's enough.

24:24.764 --> 24:27.700
[ Grunts ]
Sorry. I'm experiencing
extreme sex drive.

24:27.734 --> 24:30.202
Get in your office now.

24:30.236 --> 24:32.839
Okay. Now, what are you doing?

24:32.872 --> 24:35.642
- Are you trying to blow
this whole thing to hell?
- How do you like it,

24:35.675 --> 24:38.545
watching someone
you love self-destruct?

24:38.578 --> 24:42.649
This is your brain on drugs.

24:42.682 --> 24:45.151
I feel so close to you now.
There's no more bullshit.
No lying.

24:45.184 --> 24:47.219
Would you just put
your pants back on, please?

24:47.253 --> 24:51.223
I can't.
This is extreme sex drive.
I love you!

24:51.257 --> 24:54.026
Wayne, this is the meth talking.
You know what's happening
right now?

24:54.060 --> 24:56.729
You're gettin'
a big release of dopamine
in your prefrontal cortex.

24:56.763 --> 24:59.131
That's makes two of us.
Get off me.
Get a grip on yourself!

24:59.165 --> 25:01.834
I am not using.

25:01.868 --> 25:03.670
Yeah? I'm supposed to
believe that?

25:03.703 --> 25:06.539
Oh, my God. Why?
Do I look like you now?
That what you think?

25:06.573 --> 25:08.608
You think I'm all runnin'
around with the crazy eyes,

25:08.641 --> 25:10.677
humpin' the secretary,
rantin' about Squanto?

25:10.710 --> 25:12.845
No. I'm trying to keep
a goddamn job together.

25:12.879 --> 25:15.682
I'm trying to keep this
together, Wayne.
Do I seem like I am using?

25:15.715 --> 25:19.586
Why would I think that?
Did Hugh give you pills?

25:19.619 --> 25:23.089
No, Wayne. No, he did not.
Yeah, but he knew.
You told him.

25:23.122 --> 25:26.593
Everybody knew, Wayne.
It was goddamned obvious.
I never lied, okay?

25:26.626 --> 25:30.029
Are you gettin' me?
You are the only person
who did not know,

25:30.062 --> 25:32.098
because you were too busy
lying to yourself.

25:32.131 --> 25:34.266
Because, Wayne,
that is what you do.

25:39.338 --> 25:42.174
You stuff everything
down, Wayne.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.577
You try and make everything
look pretty.

25:44.611 --> 25:46.779
I think that's why you dragged
us here to Edenfalls,

25:46.813 --> 25:50.016
so we could live in this
glittery pretend world
and pretend to be happy.

25:52.184 --> 25:54.220
You want me to be happy?

25:54.253 --> 25:57.624
Huh? Then let me do drugs.

26:05.832 --> 26:07.634
I thought we were
in this together.

26:11.638 --> 26:13.673
Did you drive here?

26:13.706 --> 26:16.776
[ Grunts ]
Your mother's in the car.

26:18.344 --> 26:20.880
No. Don't go out there.
No, Wayne.

26:20.913 --> 26:23.215
I liberated her
from the nursing home.

26:23.249 --> 26:26.352
Look. She's completely senile.
You gotta go down
and say you're Cherien.

26:26.385 --> 26:28.955
She won't go until she knows
that Cherien is here. Cherien!
Shush!

26:28.988 --> 26:32.191
Be quiet.
[ Sniffles ]

26:32.224 --> 26:35.261
Stay here.
Do not move.

26:35.294 --> 26:37.196
I'm gonna go deal with
the old lady.

26:43.135 --> 26:45.171
Uh, he--

26:45.204 --> 26:47.073
He had an allergic reaction.

26:49.008 --> 26:51.678
To his pants?

26:53.279 --> 26:55.081
Just don't let him
leave the office.

26:57.049 --> 26:59.118
You could go buff.

26:59.151 --> 27:03.222
Buff or ecru.
Or you could even go oatmeal.

27:03.255 --> 27:06.726
And you can do
the whole thing for 500?

27:06.759 --> 27:09.095
Seeing as you're
a preferred customer.

27:11.063 --> 27:16.435
So, Doug Rich
is a lawyer for a real
estate company, huh?

27:16.468 --> 27:18.905
Uh-huh. Shoes.
[ Groans ]

27:18.938 --> 27:20.873
Oh. I'm sorry.

27:20.907 --> 27:22.842
Sorry.

27:24.376 --> 27:28.314
And his real estate company
screwed you out of $10 million?

27:28.347 --> 27:30.783
That's right.
Because of the legal action
I filed against them.

27:30.817 --> 27:32.885
Why'd you file
a legal action?

27:32.919 --> 27:35.254
Because they caused me
irreparable harm
and loss of limb.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.825
Loss of limb?

27:38.858 --> 27:41.093
No. Not my foot.
I broke that on a stair.

27:41.127 --> 27:44.964
I-It's still clearly attached
to my body. You know what?
I don't care to discuss it.

27:44.997 --> 27:47.133
Please use the stain remover
sparingly.

27:49.368 --> 27:51.270
[ Squirting ]

27:53.305 --> 27:55.407
It was your arm,
wasn't it?

27:55.441 --> 27:58.477
I believe I just said
that I didn't care
to discuss it.

27:58.510 --> 28:01.380
And now you're ruining my shag.
You know what?

28:01.413 --> 28:04.416
My paint's fine.
I do not need new paint.
You are free to go.

28:06.819 --> 28:09.455
And if you don't get
those stains off my carpet,
I will sue your ass.

28:10.522 --> 28:12.458
[ Sighs ]

28:20.867 --> 28:22.869
Oh, Jesus Christ.

28:26.138 --> 28:28.741
Hi, Mama. Hi.

28:28.775 --> 28:32.178
Oh, my goodness. Look at you.
Don't you look fine?

28:32.211 --> 28:34.947
Now, you might not
even recognize me.

28:34.981 --> 28:37.083
It's been a long time
since we've seen each other.

28:37.116 --> 28:40.052
I've had an extreme
makeover. Okay?

28:43.122 --> 28:45.457
I'm gonna take you back
to the nursing home, honey.

28:47.794 --> 28:50.329
[ Woman ]
Wanna go get some lunch?
[ Woman #2 ] Oh, I'd love to.

28:52.298 --> 28:55.134
Ah. Here we go.

28:55.167 --> 28:57.770
All right.

28:57.804 --> 28:59.738
All right.

29:01.140 --> 29:03.075
Oh, boy.

29:05.277 --> 29:09.248
Well, I've had
a personal setback today.

29:16.222 --> 29:18.124
Thanks for that.

29:28.067 --> 29:30.837
Doug's gone crazy.

29:30.870 --> 29:32.538
I think he might have
fried his brain.

29:38.477 --> 29:40.479
Your hand is warm.

29:44.116 --> 29:45.985
It's nice and warm.

29:50.556 --> 29:52.825
Kind of nice having a mama.

29:52.859 --> 29:54.994
Even a bullshit one
like you.

30:01.067 --> 30:03.936
I'm just kind of
freaked out, you know?

30:03.970 --> 30:06.472
I'm scared he might
jump off a building
when he crashes or...

30:06.505 --> 30:08.507
try and drink himself
to death because, you know,

30:08.540 --> 30:10.542
that's what you do
when you try
and numb the crash.

30:14.046 --> 30:16.182
Oh, my God.
This is so wrong.

30:17.884 --> 30:20.486
I don't know what I'm doin'.

30:20.519 --> 30:23.890
I'm not supposed to be
the strong one. I'm not.

30:26.092 --> 30:28.294
You're not Cherien.

30:32.899 --> 30:35.434
[ Phone Rings In Distance ]

30:35.467 --> 30:37.369
[ Chattering ]

30:39.371 --> 30:42.408
I'm sorry, Doug,
but since you're here,

30:42.441 --> 30:45.044
the REIT has some questions
about the documents.
What?

30:45.077 --> 30:47.113
They're kind of waiting.
Fine.

30:47.146 --> 30:49.281
[ Spitting ]

30:49.315 --> 30:52.051
Well, of course
I'm Cherien.
Y--

30:52.084 --> 30:54.553
You know?
Don't you recognize
your own daughter?

30:54.586 --> 30:57.089
You really are senile, Mom.

30:57.123 --> 30:59.458
You're not Cherien. No.

31:04.396 --> 31:08.134
I'll have
a grande mochaccino.

31:08.167 --> 31:11.470
Ooh. I gotta get you back
to the nursing home, honey.

31:11.503 --> 31:15.074
You know, I have to pee.
Okay. Well, you can pee
at the nursing home, hon.

31:15.107 --> 31:17.276
I have to pee.

31:17.309 --> 31:20.046
I have to pee!
Okay, okay, okay.
Don't pee now.

31:20.079 --> 31:22.614
I'll take you to my house.
You can pee there, okay? Okay?

31:26.185 --> 31:28.087
You're not Cherien.

31:29.721 --> 31:31.623
Cherien's a bitch.

31:34.961 --> 31:36.662
[ Sniffs ]

31:40.432 --> 31:42.601
Oh.
[ Clears Throat ]
There's, uh--

31:42.634 --> 31:48.007
Uh, there's no provision in
these contracts for our offer
to be contingent on inspection.

31:51.610 --> 31:54.346
You-- You-- You are
the head of Legal, right?

31:54.380 --> 31:57.683
Am I? Is that who I am?

32:01.320 --> 32:03.655
I'm not sure
what's real anymore.

32:03.689 --> 32:06.192
I don't think
the bugs are.

32:06.225 --> 32:09.028
You know,

32:09.061 --> 32:12.031
we run and we run
and we run,

32:12.064 --> 32:14.333
and we-- we feel
we're getting closer
to what we want,

32:14.366 --> 32:19.338
but really we're just
trying to pay
the $19,876.74 a month.

32:19.371 --> 32:22.508
I feel ya.
Try being divorced.

32:22.541 --> 32:24.710
Double everything.

32:24.743 --> 32:27.479
Try being divorced twice.
Is that who we are?

32:27.513 --> 32:29.548
Is that what's gonna be
on my tombstone?

32:29.581 --> 32:33.585
"Here lies a guy
who came up with
19,876.74 a month"?

32:33.619 --> 32:36.355
I grew up in
a Jesuit orphanage.

32:36.388 --> 32:38.024
Is this what the brothers
educated me for?

32:45.431 --> 32:48.067
I don't even remember
what I was supposed to want.

32:54.173 --> 32:56.208
If I don't have Dahlia--

33:10.422 --> 33:13.459
[ Dahlia ]
Okay. Hold on,
'cause we are almost there.

33:13.492 --> 33:16.528
Just in here.
Hi. We're home.

33:16.562 --> 33:19.731
She's senile.

33:19.765 --> 33:24.036
You're not Cherien.
She's mostly senile.

33:24.070 --> 33:28.274
It's Cherien's mom.
But I thought she was
in a nursing home.

33:28.307 --> 33:32.044
- Yeah. Your dad set her free.
- Hey, Grandma.

33:32.078 --> 33:34.680
Yeah. Grandma's
gonna go pee-pee,

33:34.713 --> 33:37.649
and then we're gonna
go back to the nice
nursing home real fast.

33:37.683 --> 33:40.386
See, I thought
both our grandmas were dead.
[ Dahlia ] Okay. Here you go.

33:40.419 --> 33:42.754
It's a miracle.

33:42.788 --> 33:45.491
[ Cell Phone Buzzing, Chirping ]

33:47.193 --> 33:49.528
Oh, Wayne. Wayne?

33:49.561 --> 33:53.432
Cherien, it's Kimmie.
Doug walked out of the office.
I couldn't stop him.

33:53.465 --> 33:56.302
And he was wearing his pants.
Oh, Jesus Christ.

33:58.704 --> 34:01.373
Oh, Wayne, please don't
do anything stupid, honey.

34:01.407 --> 34:04.443
Wayne? Wayne?

34:04.476 --> 34:07.646
Wayne. Oh, shit.
Dad didn't come home, did he?

34:07.679 --> 34:10.116
I thought Dad
was at work.
Told you he was gonna quit.

34:10.149 --> 34:12.451
Okay. Now you listen to me.

34:12.484 --> 34:14.686
You do not do
anything stupid, okay?

34:14.720 --> 34:16.655
Don't get in
any fights, please.

34:16.688 --> 34:19.191
And do not drive anywhere.
[ Thuds ]

34:19.225 --> 34:20.826
[ Sam ]
Mom, I think Grandma
fell in the bathroom.

34:23.762 --> 34:25.664
[ Knocks ]

34:27.166 --> 34:28.834
Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

34:28.867 --> 34:31.570
It has been...

34:31.603 --> 34:36.408
22 years...

34:36.442 --> 34:41.613
since my last confession,
and I have done
a shitload of meth.

34:43.182 --> 34:45.417
[ Exhales ]
Uh, my name is Doug.

34:48.487 --> 34:50.522
No.

34:50.556 --> 34:52.691
My name is Wayne.

34:52.724 --> 34:54.693
Wayne Malloy.

34:56.395 --> 34:58.597
Okay. Let's get you
in your wheelchair.

34:58.630 --> 35:01.867
Ooh. Careful there. Okay. Let's
get you back to the nursing
home, sweetheart. Okay?

35:01.900 --> 35:04.703
You're not Cherien.
No. I know, sweetheart.

35:04.736 --> 35:08.374
I made some calls.
Okay. Who'd you call?

35:08.407 --> 35:10.442
Did you call
the nursing home?

35:10.476 --> 35:12.611
Well, they're not gonna
believe you, sweetheart.

35:12.644 --> 35:14.513
I mean, you know,
you're a senile old lady.

35:14.546 --> 35:16.848
Who'd you call?

35:16.882 --> 35:19.418
She didn't call the cops,
did she?

35:19.451 --> 35:21.653
[ Chuckles ]
You're not Cherien.

35:21.687 --> 35:23.755
[ Woman On TV ]
Now, let me tell you
something, ladies.

35:23.789 --> 35:25.857
This product really works.

35:25.891 --> 35:29.561
Her doing meth--
it's because I failed her.

35:30.796 --> 35:32.831
That's why I came here.

35:32.864 --> 35:35.601
I thought if I could
build her a castle,

35:35.634 --> 35:37.869
a whole new life here
in Edenfalls, then--

35:37.903 --> 35:39.738
then I'd make it up to her.

35:42.674 --> 35:44.476
What a crock of shit.

35:46.278 --> 35:50.582
I wa--
I want to rip off my skin.

35:50.616 --> 35:53.685
I want to drink so much,
I can't even remember who I am.

35:53.719 --> 35:55.654
I want to die.

35:58.324 --> 35:59.758
I want more meth.

36:01.660 --> 36:04.830
God, you must think
I'm such an asshole.

36:04.863 --> 36:06.798
No. Of course not.

36:06.832 --> 36:09.768
You're in a lot of pain.
It's the human condition.

36:10.936 --> 36:12.938
We're all flawed, Wayne.

36:12.971 --> 36:15.207
Uh, wow.

36:15.241 --> 36:18.210
I mean, wow.
Uh, thanks.

36:18.244 --> 36:20.746
I understand how you feel.

36:20.779 --> 36:23.649
I'm having something of
an existential crisis myself.

36:23.682 --> 36:25.917
You're an existentialist
priest?

36:25.951 --> 36:28.920
I'm quitting the priesthood.
Next week is my last week.

36:28.954 --> 36:30.789
I don't believe
in God anymore.

36:31.990 --> 36:34.660
Oh, what bad timing.

36:34.693 --> 36:39.231
Stain's all scrubbed out now,
ma'am, so I'll just be
on my way.

36:39.265 --> 36:42.334
Oh. Okay. Thank you.

36:42.368 --> 36:45.671
Look. I'm sorry if I bit
your head off earlier.

36:47.306 --> 36:49.508
Oh, it's a sensitive
topic, ma'am.

36:49.541 --> 36:51.710
I can see that.

36:51.743 --> 36:54.380
So, Doug Rich--
he really screwed you over
on that paint job, huh?

36:54.413 --> 36:56.415
He can suck shit in hell
for all I care.

37:00.452 --> 37:02.821
That's Everett.
He's my husband.

37:06.792 --> 37:09.961
So you must really
hate him, huh?
Your husband?

37:09.995 --> 37:14.466
Doug Rich.
Oh, uh, yeah.

37:14.500 --> 37:17.803
Yeah. I-- Yeah.

37:17.836 --> 37:22.308
Do you? He screwed you
out of $10 million.
You must hate his guts.

37:22.341 --> 37:24.910
Probably want to
kill him.
Oh. No.

37:24.943 --> 37:29.014
[ Chuckles ] No. No. I--
I wouldn't dream of killing him.
That would be awful.

37:29.047 --> 37:32.451
I did once think of
running him over when
he was mowing his lawn,

37:32.484 --> 37:36.021
but I was very angry
that day, and I would never
really do that, of course.

37:36.054 --> 37:39.858
You know, the thing
about killin'... is, uh--

37:41.827 --> 37:45.764
My daddy passed recently,

37:45.797 --> 37:48.500
and I realized that
once a person is dead,

37:50.769 --> 37:52.838
things are always
up in the air.

37:52.871 --> 37:55.707
It's like time stands still
since the day they died.

37:57.409 --> 37:59.345
Plus they come to you
when you're asleep.

37:59.378 --> 38:02.047
My arm does that.

38:02.080 --> 38:04.750
When I dream of it,
it's still attached.

38:09.087 --> 38:11.022
Can I touch it?

38:12.391 --> 38:14.793
I'm sorry.
Uh, I just, uh--

38:14.826 --> 38:18.897
I'm kind of mechanical,
uh, and I ain't never seen
no mechanical arm before.

38:21.066 --> 38:24.035
You wouldn't be disgusted?
Oh, no.

38:29.441 --> 38:31.910
[ Whirring ]

38:35.614 --> 38:37.816
Wow.

38:40.051 --> 38:42.654
That's some solid
craftsmanship.

38:50.462 --> 38:52.664
They didn't scrimp
on them joints.

38:52.698 --> 38:55.701
I hope you weren't shocked
by what I said...

38:55.734 --> 38:58.670
about, you know,
killing Doug.

38:58.704 --> 39:01.607
I didn't mean it.
I just have very strong
feelings. That's all I meant.

39:01.640 --> 39:04.810
Yeah. I know how it is.
I've felt like that sometimes.

39:09.848 --> 39:11.817
Would you like to
stay for supper?

39:12.984 --> 39:15.454
** [ Speakers: Blues ]

39:20.125 --> 39:22.994
Keep thinking
about Squanto.
[ Grunts ]

39:23.028 --> 39:25.130
What an asshole.

39:25.163 --> 39:27.533
Upwardly mobile
son of a bitch.
Mmm.

39:27.566 --> 39:30.001
Spoke fluent English.

39:30.035 --> 39:32.103
Played everybody.
Mm-hmm.

39:38.877 --> 39:41.947
[ Woman On TV ]
All you're going to need
is this one product, ladies.

39:41.980 --> 39:45.150
Just one product.
It has only minerals
from the earth.

39:45.183 --> 39:47.986
[ Di Di Imitating
Engine Sounds ]

39:52.591 --> 39:55.193
And this color will stay on for
the next five hours, guaranteed.

39:55.226 --> 39:58.497
You know, I kind of
always wanted a grandma.

39:58.530 --> 40:01.467
No. No. Don't do that.
We're taking her back tomorrow.

40:01.500 --> 40:06.472
I know that.
I'm just saying she's just
kind of easy to talk to.

40:06.505 --> 40:08.940
She even held my hand
there for a second.

40:08.974 --> 40:11.710
So you g--
you talked to her about us?
That's great. Di Di!

40:11.743 --> 40:14.846
Calm down, Cael.
She doesn't even
understand anything, okay?

40:14.880 --> 40:17.215
I'll have a grande mochaccino.

40:17.248 --> 40:19.451
Mom, Grandma wants
another mochaccino.

40:19.485 --> 40:23.021
Mama. Geez.
I just fixed you one.

40:24.823 --> 40:26.758
[ Cell Phone Buzzing, Chirping ]

40:28.193 --> 40:30.596
Wayne,
where the hell are you?

40:30.629 --> 40:32.498
** [ Speakers: Blues ]

40:35.667 --> 40:37.769
[ Chattering ]

40:39.538 --> 40:41.172
[ Man ]
Oh, it breaks my heart.

40:44.142 --> 40:45.677
I can't drive.

40:47.679 --> 40:49.681
Father Jeff took the bus.

40:51.082 --> 40:53.218
I want to die.

40:55.220 --> 40:57.055
It's gonna go away
after a while.

40:59.658 --> 41:01.527
Is this how you felt?

41:05.631 --> 41:07.566
Yeah.

41:10.101 --> 41:12.237
I'm so sorry.

41:13.872 --> 41:15.874
Yeah.

41:15.907 --> 41:17.843
Oh, man.

41:19.077 --> 41:21.012
I was so ashamed, Wayne.

41:22.681 --> 41:24.550
I couldn't tell you.

41:29.921 --> 41:32.157
I wanted to make you
this beautiful life.

41:32.190 --> 41:34.860
[ Chuckles ]

41:37.963 --> 41:39.931
But it's not real.

41:50.709 --> 41:52.611
Come on. Let's go.

41:58.083 --> 42:00.085
You don't want your shoes?
No.

42:00.118 --> 42:02.520
No? Okay.
[ Mutters ]

42:04.823 --> 42:08.093
[ Murmurs ]
My buttons are falling off.
What?

42:08.126 --> 42:11.262
My buttons are falling off.
Your but-- Okay. Let me see.
Let me see. Let me see.

42:15.233 --> 42:17.535
You scared the shit
out of me today.

42:20.238 --> 42:24.142
All I could picture was you
lyin' dead in some hospital
somewhere from an overdose.

42:25.744 --> 42:27.646
Oh.
[ Sniffles ]

42:30.181 --> 42:33.719
Hey. Are we big enough
for this life?

42:33.752 --> 42:36.722
Are we big enough
for this crazy world
we found ourself in?

42:36.755 --> 42:38.624
'Cause I don't know.

42:39.925 --> 42:42.027
I've messed up
your whole life.

42:42.060 --> 42:44.963
[ Chuckles ]

42:44.996 --> 42:46.998
Yeah. You have.

42:47.032 --> 42:49.935
[ Chuckles ]

42:49.968 --> 42:51.903
Baby,

42:54.205 --> 42:56.775
all I ever wanted was
a messed-up life with you.

43:02.413 --> 43:04.315
Without you,

43:08.687 --> 43:11.623
I can't do my buttons.

43:11.657 --> 43:13.358
[ Dahlia Laughs ]

43:17.929 --> 43:19.965
Mmm.
[ Chuckles ]

43:19.998 --> 43:22.400
You're so--
I want to go home.

43:22.433 --> 43:25.403
You're so pathetic.
Come here.

43:25.436 --> 43:27.338
** [ Continues ]

43:29.307 --> 43:31.209
** [ Fades ]
